cs.MOBILE, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper focuses on offloading work to the cloud to increase the battery life of mobile devices, which is a key concern in mobile computing. Therefore, cs.MOBILE is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges and constraints of implementing offloading in network-intensive applications, which falls under the domain of distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed toolkit, SmartDiet, provides fine-grained offloading constraint identification and energy usage analysis, which involves system-level considerations (cs.SY) and software engineering principles (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a solution for creating energy-efficient code, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
